29/09/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Speaking on Tuesday (28 September), Republika Srpska's (RS) new interior minister, Darko Matijasevic, pledged full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, including detention of indictees. Matijasevic told a news conference that his ministry would implement all obligations spelled out in the RS law on co-operation with The Hague tribunal. 
In other news Tuesday, SFOR announced the release of Bosnian Serb Milovan Cicko Bjelica. He was detained four weeks ago for purportedly aiding fugitive indictee Radovan Karadzic. (Nezavisne novine - 29/09/04; PBS BiH, AFP - 28/09/04) 
